  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Progressive Shelter through the Spanish Red Cross</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Affected populations, Internally displaced persons (IDPs)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To meet the longer term housing needs of those displaced by the earthquake, the American Red Cross partnered with the Spanish Red Cross to upgrade transitional shelters into permanent homes. Through this partnership, the American Red Cross provided funding to purchase materials needed to reinforce 4,427 transitional shelters that are already being built by the Spanish and Haitian Red Cross societies so that they can serve as permanent homes, as well as to construct 1,500 latrines. Community members in Leogane were involved in the construction process, learning skills they can apply to future jobs.</narrative>
  </description>
